  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Introduction",
      "level": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "This report presents the structural assessment for the adaptive reuse of an existing warehouse at the Maashaven district in Rotterdam. The former industrial building (built 1962) is being converted into a mixed-use development comprising offices, co-working spaces, and a ground floor food hall."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The existing structure consists of a reinforced concrete frame with precast floor slabs, supported on driven precast concrete piles. A new steel mezzanine floor is introduced at level +4.50 m to create additional usable area within the existing double-height ground floor."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "• Gross floor area (existing): 4,200 m²<br/>• Gross floor area (new mezzanine): 1,850 m²<br/>• Number of floors: 3 (ground + 2 upper) + new mezzanine<br/>• Building height: 14.8 m (existing, unchanged)<br/>• Structural system: RC frame with new steel insertions<br/>• Foundation: existing driven precast piles (350×350 mm)"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Scope and limitations",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "This report covers the following structural elements:"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "• Assessment of existing RC frame capacity for the new loading regime<br/>• Design of new steel mezzanine floor (beams + columns)<br/>• Verification of existing foundation for increased loads<br/>• Local reinforcement details at new openings<br/>• Stability check of the overall structure"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "<b>Excluded from scope:</b> MEP penetrations, facade connections, temporary works during construction, and seismic assessment (not required per NEN-EN 1998 NA for consequence class CC2 in the Netherlands)."
        }
      ]
    },

