    {
      "title": "Loading",
      "level": 1,
      "page_break_before": true,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Loads are determined in accordance with NEN-EN 1991. The existing structure is assessed for the new loading regime resulting from the change of function from warehouse (category E) to office/commercial (category B/D)."
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Permanent loads",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "table",
          "title": "Permanent loads (characteristic)",
          "headers": ["Load component", "Value", "Unit", "Reference"],
          "rows": [
            ["RC slab self-weight (200 mm)", "5.00", "kN/m²", "NEN-EN 1991-1-1"],
            ["Composite floor deck (new mezzanine)", "2.80", "kN/m²", "Supplier datasheet"],
            ["Floor finish — raised access floor", "0.40", "kN/m²", "NEN-EN 1991-1-1 A.2"],
            ["Floor finish — screed (40 mm)", "0.80", "kN/m²", "NEN-EN 1991-1-1 A.2"],
            ["Suspended ceiling + services", "0.25", "kN/m²", "Estimate"],
            ["MEP installations (allowance)", "0.50", "kN/m²", "MEP engineer"],
            ["Lightweight partitions (moveable)", "0.50", "kN/m²", "NEN-EN 1991-1-1 §6.3.1.2"],
            ["Facade cladding (curtain wall)", "0.80", "kN/m", "Facade consultant"]
          ]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Variable loads",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "table",
          "title": "Variable loads (characteristic)",
          "headers": ["Category", "Description", "q_k [kN/m²]", "Q_k [kN]"],
          "rows": [
            ["B", "Office areas", "2.50", "3.0"],
            ["C1", "Co-working / meeting rooms", "3.00", "4.0"],
            ["D1", "Food hall (ground floor)", "5.00", "7.0"],
            ["H", "Roofs — maintenance only", "1.00", "1.5"],
            ["—", "Mezzanine (office use)", "2.50", "3.0"]
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "<b>Note:</b> The original warehouse was designed for category E1 (q_k = 7.5 kN/m²). The new function reduces the imposed floor load on the upper floors, but the ground floor food hall load exceeds the original residential-adjacent zones."
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Wind loads",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Wind loads are determined per NEN-EN 1991-1-4 with Dutch National Annex. The building is located in wind area II (coastal zone), terrain category II (harbour area with limited obstructions)."
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Basic wind velocity",
          "formula": "v_b = c_dir × c_season × v_b,0",
          "substitution": "v_b = 1.0 × 1.0 × 27.0",
          "result": "27.0",
          "unit": "m/s",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1991-1-4 §4.2"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Peak velocity pressure at building height",
          "formula": "q_p(z) = c_e(z) × q_b",
          "substitution": "q_p(14.8) = 2.95 × 0.456",
          "result": "1.35",
          "unit": "kN/m²",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1991-1-4 §4.5"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Snow loads",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Snow load on roof",
          "formula": "s = μ_i × C_e × C_t × s_k",
          "substitution": "s = 0.8 × 1.0 × 1.0 × 0.70",
          "result": "0.56",
          "unit": "kN/m²",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1991-1-3 §5.2"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Roof shape coefficient μ_1 = 0.8 for flat roof (0° ≤ α ≤ 30°). Ground snow load s_k = 0.70 kN/m² (zone 3, Netherlands)."
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Load combinations",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Load combinations are determined per NEN-EN 1990 §6.4.3, using partial factors from Table A1.2(B) — set B for STR/GEO design situations."
        },
        {
          "type": "table",
          "title": "ULS load combinations (STR/GEO)",
          "headers": ["Comb.", "Permanent", "Imposed", "Wind", "Snow", "Governing"],
          "rows": [
            ["LC1", "1.35 G", "1.50 Q", "0.90 W", "0.75 S", "Floors"],
            ["LC2", "1.35 G", "1.05 Q", "1.50 W", "0.75 S", "Stability"],
            ["LC3", "1.35 G", "1.05 Q", "0.90 W", "1.50 S", "Roof"],
            ["LC4", "1.20 G", "—", "1.50 W", "—", "Uplift"],
            ["LC5", "1.35 G", "1.50 Q", "—", "—", "Settlement"]
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "table",
          "title": "SLS load combinations (characteristic)",
          "headers": ["Comb.", "Permanent", "Imposed", "Wind", "Snow"],
          "rows": [
            ["SLS1", "1.0 G", "1.0 Q", "0.6 W", "0.5 S"],
            ["SLS2", "1.0 G", "0.7 Q", "1.0 W", "0.5 S"],
            ["SLS3", "1.0 G", "0.7 Q", "0.6 W", "1.0 S"]
          ]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Existing structure — assessment",
      "level": 1,
      "page_break_before": true,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The existing RC frame is assessed according to NEN 8700 for the new loading conditions. The assessment uses reduced reliability levels appropriate for existing structures (β = 3.3 for CC2, remaining life > 15 years)."
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Existing beam B2.1 — 400×600 mm",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Primary beam B2.1 spans 8.40 m on the second floor. Cross-section: 400×600 mm, reinforcement 4Ø25 bottom + 2Ø20 top (confirmed by scan and local exposure). Concrete cover c_nom = 30 mm."
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Design bending moment (new loading)",
          "formula": "M_Ed = q_Ed × L² / 8",
          "substitution": "M_Ed = 18.2 × 8.40² / 8",
          "result": "160.5",
          "unit": "kNm",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1992-1-1 §6.1"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Bending resistance existing beam",
          "formula": "M_Rd = A_s × f_yd × (d − 0.4x)",
          "substitution": "M_Rd = 1963 × 209 × (555 − 0.4 × 48.3) × 10⁻⁶",
          "result": "219.3",
          "unit": "kNm",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1992-1-1 §6.1"
        },
        {
          "type": "check",
          "description": "Unity check — bending existing beam B2.1",
          "required_value": "UC ≤ 1.0",
          "calculated_value": "M_Ed / M_Rd = 160.5 / 219.3",
          "unity_check": 0.73,
          "limit": 1.0,
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1992-1-1 §6.1"
        },
        {
          "type": "spacer",
          "height_mm": 4
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Design shear force",
          "formula": "V_Ed = q_Ed × L / 2",
          "substitution": "V_Ed = 18.2 × 8.40 / 2",
          "result": "76.4",
          "unit": "kN",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1992-1-1 §6.2"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Shear resistance (without shear reinforcement)",
          "formula": "V_Rd,c = [C_Rd,c × k × (100 × ρ_l × f_ck)^(1/3)] × b_w × d",
          "substitution": "V_Rd,c = [0.12 × 1.60 × (100 × 0.0089 × 28.5)^(1/3)] × 400 × 555 × 10⁻³",
          "result": "112.8",
          "unit": "kN",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1992-1-1 §6.2.2"
        },
        {
          "type": "check",
          "description": "Unity check — shear existing beam B2.1",
          "required_value": "V_Ed ≤ V_Rd,c (no shear reinforcement required)",
          "calculated_value": "V_Ed / V_Rd,c = 76.4 / 112.8",
          "unity_check": 0.68,
          "limit": 1.0,
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1992-1-1 §6.2.2"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Existing column K.A3 — 400×400 mm",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Interior column K.A3 at grid intersection A-3. Cross-section: 400×400 mm, reinforcement 4Ø25 (confirmed). Free height: 3.60 m (ground floor). Buckling length factor β = 0.7 (restrained both ends)."
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Design axial load",
          "formula": "N_Ed = ΣR_beams + G_column",
          "substitution": "N_Ed = 842 + 24",
          "result": "866",
          "unit": "kN",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1992-1-1 §6.1"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Axial capacity existing column",
          "formula": "N_Rd = A_c × f_cd + A_s × f_yd",
          "substitution": "N_Rd = 160000 × 18.7 + 1963 × 209",
          "result": "3403",
          "unit": "kN",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1992-1-1 §6.1"
        },
        {
          "type": "check",
          "description": "Unity check — axial capacity column K.A3",
          "required_value": "UC ≤ 1.0",
          "calculated_value": "N_Ed / N_Rd = 866 / 3403",
          "unity_check": 0.25,
          "limit": 1.0,
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1992-1-1 §6.1"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "<b>Conclusion:</b> Existing column K.A3 has significant reserve capacity (UC = 0.25). The reduced imposed load from office use (vs. original warehouse use) results in lower axial forces than the original design."
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "New mezzanine structure",
      "level": 1,
      "page_break_before": true,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "A new steel mezzanine floor is introduced at level +4.50 m within the existing double-height ground floor. The mezzanine spans between new steel columns, which transfer loads directly to the existing pile caps. The mezzanine is structurally independent from the existing RC frame to avoid load redistribution."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "• Main beams: HEB 360, S355 — spanning 10.20 m<br/>• Secondary beams: IPE 270, S235 — spanning 5.10 m at 2.55 m c/c<br/>• Columns: HEB 200, S355 — height 4.50 m<br/>• Floor: Composite steel deck with 120 mm concrete topping<br/>• Connection to existing structure: lateral restraint only (no vertical load transfer)"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Main beam MB1 — HEB 360",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Main beam MB1 spans 10.20 m, supporting 4 secondary beams at 2.55 m spacing. Profile: HEB 360, steel S355. The beam is laterally restrained at secondary beam connections."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "<b>Bending verification</b>",
          "style": "Heading3"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Line load on main beam",
          "formula": "q_Ed = (g_k × γ_G + q_k × γ_Q) × tributary width",
          "substitution": "q_Ed = (4.45 × 1.35 + 2.50 × 1.50) × 5.10",
          "result": "49.7",
          "unit": "kN/m",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1990 §6.4.3"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Design bending moment",
          "formula": "M_Ed = q_Ed × L² / 8",
          "substitution": "M_Ed = 49.7 × 10.20² / 8",
          "result": "646.1",
          "unit": "kNm",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Plastic moment resistance",
          "formula": "M_pl,Rd = W_pl,y × f_y / γ_M0",
          "substitution": "M_pl,Rd = 2683e3 × 355 / 1.0",
          "result": "952.5",
          "unit": "kNm",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1 §6.2.5"
        },
        {
          "type": "check",
          "description": "Unity check — bending main beam MB1",
          "required_value": "UC ≤ 1.0",
          "calculated_value": "M_Ed / M_pl,Rd = 646.1 / 952.5",
          "unity_check": 0.68,
          "limit": 1.0,
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1 §6.2.5"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "<b>Shear verification</b>",
          "style": "Heading3"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Design shear force",
          "formula": "V_Ed = q_Ed × L / 2",
          "substitution": "V_Ed = 49.7 × 10.20 / 2",
          "result": "253.5",
          "unit": "kN",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1 §6.2.6"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Plastic shear resistance",
          "formula": "V_pl,Rd = A_v × (f_y / √3) / γ_M0",
          "substitution": "V_pl,Rd = 5765 × (355 / 1.732) / 1.0",
          "result": "1181.3",
          "unit": "kN",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1 §6.2.6"
        },
        {
          "type": "check",
          "description": "Unity check — shear main beam MB1",
          "required_value": "V_Ed ≤ 0.5 V_pl,Rd (low shear — no interaction required)",
          "calculated_value": "V_Ed / V_pl,Rd = 253.5 / 1181.3",
          "unity_check": 0.21,
          "limit": 1.0,
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1 §6.2.6"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "<b>Deflection verification</b>",
          "style": "Heading3"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Maximum deflection (SLS)",
          "formula": "δ = 5 × q_sls × L⁴ / (384 × E × I)",
          "substitution": "δ = 5 × 35.8 × 10200⁴ / (384 × 210000 × 43190e4)",
          "result": "33.8",
          "unit": "mm",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1 §7.2"
        },
        {
          "type": "check",
          "description": "Unity check — deflection main beam MB1",
          "required_value": "δ ≤ L/250 = 40.8 mm",
          "calculated_value": "δ / δ_max = 33.8 / 40.8",
          "unity_check": 0.83,
          "limit": 1.0,
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1 §7.2"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Secondary beam SB1 — IPE 270",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Secondary beam SB1 spans 5.10 m between main beams. Profile: IPE 270, steel S235. Simply supported, laterally restrained by the composite floor deck."
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Design bending moment",
          "formula": "M_Ed = q_Ed × L² / 8",
          "substitution": "M_Ed = 25.0 × 5.10² / 8",
          "result": "81.3",
          "unit": "kNm",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1"
        },
        {
          "type": "calculation",
          "title": "Plastic moment resistance",
          "formula": "M_pl,Rd = W_pl,y × f_y / γ_M0",
          "substitution": "M_pl,Rd = 484e3 × 235 / 1.0",
          "result": "113.7",
          "unit": "kNm",
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1 §6.2.5"
        },
        {
          "type": "check",
          "description": "Unity check — bending secondary beam SB1",
          "required_value": "UC ≤ 1.0",
          "calculated_value": "M_Ed / M_pl,Rd = 81.3 / 113.7",
          "unity_check": 0.72,
          "limit": 1.0,
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1 §6.2.5"
        },
        {
          "type": "check",
          "description": "Unity check — deflection secondary beam SB1",
          "required_value": "δ ≤ L/250 = 20.4 mm",
          "calculated_value": "δ = 14.1 mm",
          "unity_check": 0.69,
          "limit": 1.0,
          "reference": "NEN-EN 1993-1-1 §7.2"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "title": "Mezzanine column MC1 — HEB 200",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
